gmd:description.gco:CharacterString:
All  CNTR 2010 feature classes were based on common repository data (COMM_PLUS). These are collections of geometry from different sources which contain all geometry necessary to created the different feature classes for the datasets COMM, NUTS, CNTR and COAS. The creation of the common repository data is a complex process with a lot of manual handling. This dataset COMM_PLUS served as a base for the lower scale levels of the NUTS, CNTR and COAS datasets
 Here only the process steps after the creation of the common repository are briefly described
Step 1: The first step was to create an empty database schema for the CNTR_2010 dataset;
Step 2: Pre-processing data to prepare the common repository (COMM_PLUS) them to load into the new Geodatabase structure which included: 
       (i) if necessary, COMM_PLUS was generalized on the scale levels 1M, 3M, 10M, 20M and 60M;
       (ii) clean data with correct precision;
       (iii) derive the regions for the CNTR level;
       (iv) derive the CNTR boundary from the regions.
       (v) derivation of a table that defines relationship between boundaries and regions based on spatial relation;
       (vi) attribute manipulation to match the new structure;
       (vii) topology correction;
Step 3: the preprocessed feature classes were loaded in the empty geodatabase schema for the CNTR_2010 dataset;
Step 4: adding metadata

- For the Labels (CNTR_LB_2010):
The input for this label feature class was prepared in Arctool box of ARCGIS based on the regions of the CNTR_RG_100K_2010 feature class.

It has been respected the following rules:

a.) One label point per region;
b.) The label point must be inside of the region in case of single part regions;
c.) In case of multipart regions: the label point will be situated in the part which covers more then 50% of the total area. If there is no part covering more the 50% of the total area then the label point will be placed in the center of gravity of the region.

The resulting label were loaded with the simple data loader of ArcGIS to the feature class CNTR_LB_2010.

- For the Capitals of the World
The Capitals of the World feature class were based in the Esri dataset.
 Here only the process steps after  creation of the common repository are briefly described
Step 1: Once the dataset CNTR_2010 was ready, was loaded the shape files Cities.shp in the feature class CNTR_CAPT_PT_2010
Step 2:  Attribute manipulation to match the new structure;
Step 3: Correct the location of the cities;
Step 4: Topology correction
Step 5: adding metadata
